Fast JSON Parser for .NET

39% less time than Newtonsoft.Json using 31% less memory. (Comparison by deserializing and reserializing a relatively
small JSON document.)

Uses ReadOnlyMemory<char> instead of string.

Does not parse JSON literals to value types, such as true, false, null or numbers. Since JSON numbers are not bounded
by rules of IEEE 754 floating point, they can be arbitrarily large or precise.

Kept fairly simple. No dependencies. No support for JSONPath or LINQ to JSON. No support for deserialization to .NET
objects or serialization from them. No support for JSON Schema. No support for JSON5.